        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Step 1: Draft with Claude</h2>
        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Open Claude Desktop</h4>
                    <p>Launch the app on your computer. You'll see a chat window.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Copy a prompt from the <a href="/prompts/">Prompts page</a></h4>
                    <p>Pick the prompt that matches what you're updating. Each prompt tells you which CMS section to use.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Paste, customize, and run</h4>
                    <p>Replace the [brackets] with your real details. Press Enter. Review the output and iterate until you're happy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="walkthrough-example">
            <h4>Example: Adding a volunteer opportunity</h4>
            <div class="prompt-text" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
                <code>I'm updating the Reach for Youth volunteer page. I need to add a new volunteer opportunity to the CMS.

The CMS has these fields for each opportunity:
1. Title — the role name
2. Details — 3-5 bullet points (what they'll do, time commitment, qualifications)

New role to add:
- Youth Workshop Facilitator
- Saturday mornings, twice per month
- Leading life-skills workshops for teens 13-17
- No experience needed, training provided

Write the title and 3 detail bullets. Welcoming tone. Draft 2 versions so I can pick my favorite.</code>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

